comments: Bamba (PHI) jumps vertically and absorbs the contact with Sexton (UTA) as he makes the pass.
Oubre Jr. (PHI) reaches across Collins' (UTA) right arm and makes contact with the ball, before making incidental contact with his hand on the ball.
Beverley (PHI) gathers the ball on his left foot and takes three steps before he passes the ball.
Fontecchio (UTA) moves alongside Maxey's (PHI) path and absorbs the marginal body contact initiated by Maxey during the driving shot attempt.
Beverley (PHI) legally contests Markkanen's (UTA) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Fontecchio (UTA) initiates illegal contact to Harris's (PHI) face as he gains possession of the rebound.
Maxey (PHI) is late to the spot and initiates contact to Sexton's (UTA) side, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Sexton (UTA) places his hand on Maxey's (PHI) right arm on the perimeter and Maxey raises his own arm, drawing attention to the marginal contact.
Clarkson (UTA) is moving alongside Maxey's (PHI) path and Maxey loses his balance on his own.

Replay review of the foul called on Collins (UTA) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful.  Collins cleanly blocks Oubre Jr.'s (PHI) dunk attempt and any contact with his arm is marginal.
Collins (UTA) is moving alongside Maxey's (PHI) path and Maxey drives directly into him.  The resulting body contact is marginal.
Clarkson (UTA) commits a take foul on Harris (PHI).
Bamba (PHI) and Collins (UTA) engage with one another and results in contact with a game official.  Both players are assessed a technical foul.
Bamba (PHI) and Collins (UTA) engage with one another and results in contact with a game official.  Both players are assessed a technical foul.
Sexton (UTA) commits a take foul on Maxey (PHI).
Maxey (PHI) commits a take foul on Clarkson (UTA).  The illegal contact occurs before Clarkson begins his shooting motion and a non-shooting foul is correctly assessed.
